A vintage-style illustration depicting two distinct mechanical clockwork systems - one crafted from warm brass gears and copper pipes representing legacy enterprise technology, the other from sleek silver components and delicate springs representing web scripting - merging together in the center where their cogs interlock perfectly. The scene is set on an old mahogany workbench scattered with technical blueprints and drafting tools. Soft amber light from an unseen window casts long shadows across the intricate machinery. The color palette features rich sepia tones, aged patina greens, and burnished metallic highlights, evoking a 1920s engineering workshop aesthetic.
